    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2003 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering linear torque and a distinct horizontally-opposed acoustic profile. Meticulously maintained for the driving enthusiast, it features a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS) to ensure structural integrity. The 6-speed manual transaxle offers precise gate engagement, while the chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B6 dampers for superior damping control and reduced body roll during high-G cornering. Riding on staggered alloys with high-performance rubber, the mechanical grip and turn-in response are exceptional. Though the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its well-loved status, the drivetrain remains robust and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback purists crave.",
